  "text": "Model checking of hybrid systems is usually expressed in terms of the following reachability problem for hybrid automata (HA) [CITATION_1] : given an HA M, a set of initial states I , and a set of unsafe states U , determine whether there exists a trajectory of M starting in an initial state and ending in an unsafe state. The time-bounded version of this problem considers trajectories that are within a given time bound T .",
